Medicare has a toll-free hotline and a Web site to help people sort through the new Part D drug coverage. If you want Medicare to help you compare drug plans, here are a few suggestions. 1) Have your Medicare card and a list of all your medications handy. BY TELEPHONE Medicare has hired 8,000 people to answer questions about the drug benefit and they are still learning their jobs. The fastest way to talk to a live person is to select ``enrollment.'' 3) After listing some pertinent dates, you will be asked to select either ``enrollment'' ``information'' or ``publication.'' 